                                  About Us

   Governor's Office for Innovation in Government
   Governor Gray Davis created the Office for Innovation in Government  to
   improve customer service, focusing on those state practices and
   processes that have the most direct and significant impact on
   Californians.  More...
   At your service
   The staff of the Governor's Office for Innovation in Government is
   available to consult with state departments in support of improvement
   efforts. More...

                                 What's New

   Innovation in Government Annual Report
   The Governor's Office for Innovation in Government's Annual Report
   highlights the office's goals and accomplishments and includes brief
   summaries of some innovative projects being implemented by State
   departments. More...

   January Innovation-Gram
   This month's update from the Governor's Office for Innovation in
   Government highlights the upcoming Executive Leadership Forum on
   information security, plus reports on the new "Clarity Award," "Public
   Service Excellence Award," tips for coping with bureaucracy and this
   year's winners of the California Awards for Performance Excellence.
   More...

   Clarity Award
   Governor's Office for Innovation in Government has initiated
   California's "Clarity Award" program with the goal to simplify the
   language used in state government documents. The Clarity Award program
   involves reducing complexity and verbosity in documents, from pamphlets
   and loan applications to everyday forms and regulations. Applications
   are now being accepted. More...



